Kenyans with adequate doses of the vaccines, the issue of affordability sticks out like a sore thumb. Since the Alma-Ata Declaration of 1978, many countries have adopted the concept of essential medicines. As the world celebrates the discovery of several vaccines that can ameliorate the spread of SARS-CoV-2, the all-important issue of access to these lifesaving technologies in developing countries cannot be ignored.



